<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  people who obviously think “more guns” is the way to a peaceful existence. I cannot think how basic logic can be skewed in such a fashion as to justify this view. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Tell ya what. That guy plans on breaking into your home and robbing you/killing you and your family. <br>
<br>
Now, who do you think he's going to target given the options:<br>
<br>
1 - Unarmed<br>
2 - The guy that owns firearms and knows how to use em.<br>
<br>
Break in my home and take my stuff, no sweat. That's why I have insurance. Break in and wish to harm my family, better be ready to fight for it. I do shoot back.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  do your local law enforcement personnel agree with you? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, here, they DO agree. Do they condone citizens owning assault rifles? Nope. Has the police department here publicly stated that they believe citizens should have a weapon (and the training to go with it) for self defense? yup.<br>
<br>
Wanna know what type? 38 revolver for the person that isnt a sport shooter. In the self defense calss my wife took, taught by our police department, that's what they suggested. Reason being a revolver is a simple handgun to operate if you only own it for self defense.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  of all crimes committed with a handgun “80% were obtained from family, friends, a street buy, or an illegal source”. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't doubt that for a min. Read it again. That doesn't say 80% come from some dude with a trunk full of assault rifles.  Your statement about cruising out to the &quot;hood&quot; and picking up a gun is BS.<br>
<br>
Oh, you forgot to read ALL of that page didnt you?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  During the offense that brought them to prison, 15% of State inmates and 13% of Federal inmates carried a handgun, and about 2%, a military-style semiautomatic gun. <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
<br>
2% You do see that right? That is semiautomatic too. That covers a whole lot of guns INCLUDING a reminton 1100 shotgun used for quail hunting.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
On average, State inmates possessing a firearm received sentences of 18 years, while those without a weapon had an average sentence of 12 years. <br>
Among prisoners carrying a firearm during their crime, 40% of State inmates and 56% of Federal inmates received a sentence enhancement because of<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
